				\begin{document}$$\chi$$\end{document}χ2) tests. The underlying assumptions of parametric tests were checked with the Kolmogorov–Smirnov test and Levene’s test. A missing data evaluation was carried out, and missing values were imputed by applying the expectation maximization (EM) algorithm. All data were checked for plausibility. The primary data analysis strategy was intention to treat (ITT). Participants who dropped out during the intervention period were subsequently interviewed and included in the ITT analyses. Dropout analyses were calculated to check for differences between participants who dropped out and those who completed the study, using χ2 tests and t tests for independent samples.
